headlines.description: — Jayson Tatum had 25 points and 10 rebounds, Sam Hauser poured in 25 points on seven 3s and the Boston Celtics avenged an early season loss to the Charlotte Hornets with a 118-104 victory on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jayson Tatum, Sam Hauser each score 25 as Celtics beat Hornets 118-104 for 11th win in 13 games

headlines.description: — Jaren Jackson Jr. scored 27 of his 40 points in the second half and the Memphis Grizzlies held on for a 110-108 victory over the Detroit Pistons on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jaren Jackson Jr. scores 40, Grizzlies hang on to beat Pistons 110-108

headlines.description: — Tyrese Haliburton scored 27 points and had 13 assists to lead the Indiana Pacers to a 133-111 rout of the Brooklyn Nets on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tyrese Haliburton helps Pacers surge past Nets 133-111

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Orlando Magic

headlines.description: — The Portland Trail Blazers' 10th straight loss came down to one shot, and it was a good one.
headlines.shortLinkText: Franz Wagner scores 20, Magic escape with a 104-103 win over struggling Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Vit Krejci felt as if the ball was going to go in with each shot.
headlines.shortLinkText: Vit Krejci sets career highs with 18 points, 6 3s as Hawks beat Bulls 113-101

events.name: Phoenix Suns at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Devin Booker scored 52 points, the fifth-highest scoring game of his career, to power the Phoenix Suns to a 124-111 victory over the New Orleans Pelicans on Monday night, bringing them within a game of the Pelicans for the No. 6 playoff spot in the...
headlines.shortLinkText: Devin Booker scores 52 points to lift the Suns over the Pelicans 124-111
